                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d833">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">836.48 1930 Hurricane/1: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-04T09:00:00-04:40"
                            >September 4, 1930—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 10:55 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. City and environs 99 percent destroyed. President agrees with my request that
                    Red Cross rush food, light clothing, shelter, medicines and sanitary unit. Urge
                    sending warship with supplier immediately. No reports yet from interior. Loss of
                    life here appears small.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Curtis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
